-- @id: R3-periodcontrol
-- @gap: C1,C2
-- @risk: medium
-- @type: sql
-- @description: Provision fiscal calendar/year/periods + period control and wire org period control for tenants onboarded before period-control wiring existed
--
-- Hand-built, FROZEN migration. There is no generator at apply time; the static
-- body below was produced once, by hand, from the GOClient sampledata XMLs
-- (C_CALENDAR / C_YEAR / C_PERIOD / C_PERIODCONTROL) and frozen here.
--   * Source comes from the SHIPPED sampledata, NOT a live DB read: the GOAdmin /
--     GOOrg source clients may be absent in production, so the operative fiscal
--     block is staged from XML and frozen here.
--   * Source ids are written as @uuid_<srcid>@ labels. At apply time the runner
--     makes a temp copy and replaces every label with a fresh per-tenant id
--     (same label => same id, so intra-set FKs stay linked: year->calendar,
--     period->year, periodcontrol->period). A new tenant gets a brand-new id set
--     => ZERO cross-client references. The file on disk never changes.
--   * Tenant client/org are written as :client_id / :org_id and baked per tenant.
--     Every source row belongs to the operative org (never '0').
--   * The whole @apply runs in ONE transaction (runner wraps BEGIN/COMMIT); on
--     failure it rolls back and the chain halts for that tenant.
--
-- CRUCIAL CAVEAT — why plain INSERT ... VALUES with NO WHERE NOT EXISTS guards:
--   Broken tenants ALREADY have an UNWIRED calendar / year / 12 periods, named
--   IDENTICALLY to the source (calendar "... Calendar", year 2026, periods
--   Mar-26 ...). What they lack is c_periodcontrol AND the org period-control
--   wiring. A natural-key WHERE NOT EXISTS guard would wrongly MATCH those
--   pre-existing 2026 / Mar-26 rows, skip the inserts, and leave the new
--   periodcontrol pointing at periods that were never inserted (orphaned).
--   So this fix inserts a FRESH, fully wired fiscal block and intentionally
--   leaves the tenant's old unwired block dangling -- exactly as R1 leaves the
--   orphan account-element tree. Idempotency therefore comes SOLELY from @check
--   (the org has no period control), never from per-row guards.

-- @check
-- Needs the fix when an operative org has NO period control rows at all (C2),
-- which also implies the org was never wired for period control (C1).
SELECT 1
FROM ad_org o
WHERE o.ad_client_id = :client_id
  AND o.ad_org_id <> '0'
  AND o.isactive = 'Y'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM c_periodcontrol pc WHERE pc.ad_org_id = o.ad_org_id);

-- @apply
-- Insertion order (parents first); all rows are plain INSERT ... VALUES (see caveat above):
--   1. C_CALENDAR       3. C_PERIOD
--   2. C_YEAR           4. C_PERIODCONTROL
-- then C1: wire the operative org to the fresh calendar.

-- 1. C_CALENDAR  (the operative fiscal calendar; source name "GOOrg Calendar"
--    becomes "@name_client@ Calendar" so it is branded per tenant AND distinct
--    from the tenant's pre-existing unwired calendar of the same source name).
--    em_intr_isintrastat (Intrastat module column, em_ prefix) is intentionally
--    omitted: it carries a DB default ('Y') and only exists when that optional
--    localization module is installed, so listing it would add a needless
--    cross-module dependency to this corrective.

-- 2. C_YEAR  (FK c_calendar_id -> the fresh calendar above).

-- 3. C_PERIOD  (12 monthly periods, FK c_year_id -> the fresh year above).
--    openclose is set by the open-through-June rule, not the source snapshot:
--    'C' (open period) for Jan..Jun, 'O' (closed/never-opened) for Jul..Dec.

-- 4. C_PERIODCONTROL  (516 rows; FK c_period_id -> one of the 12 fresh periods).
--    processing is nullable and absent in the source XML -> null.
--    periodstatus/openclose follow the open-through-June rule (periodaction stays
--    'N'): Jan..Jun => Open ('O','C'); Jul..Dec => Never opened ('N','O').

-- ===========================================================================
-- C1. Wire the operative org to the FRESH calendar and enable period control,
--     mirroring the golden GOOrg configuration. (This is the C1 gap.)
UPDATE ad_org SET
  isperiodcontrolallowed = 'Y',
  c_calendar_id = '@uuid_120C03C5A8C84607B27794CA13DB15B1@',
  ad_inheritedcalendar_id = '@uuid_120C03C5A8C84607B27794CA13DB15B1@',
  ad_periodcontrolallowed_org_id = :org_id,
  ad_calendarowner_org_id = :org_id,
  updated = now(), updatedby = '0'
WHERE ad_org_id = :org_id;
